This article is a Presidential Proclamation by Barack Obama declaring May 1, 2010, as Law Day, U.S.A. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of the rule of law in maintaining a safe, free, and just society. It recognizes the need to adapt legal traditions to meet the challenges of the 21st century, including issues related to human rights, criminal justice, intellectual property, business transactions, and environmental regulation. The proclamation encourages Americans to reflect on and renew their commitment to legal traditions and calls for appropriate ceremonies and activities to acknowledge the importance of the nation's legal and judicial systems.